main event: A civilian reported seeing 3 unidentified objects in the sky near Jacksonville, Pennsylvania on June 21, 1952.
interesting points: The report was part of Project Blue Book, which documented UFO sightings for the U.S. Air Force., The observation was classified as ground-visual., No photographs or physical evidence were provided with the report., The report concluded that there was insufficient data for evaluation., The objects were reported as being observed at a specific course of 33 degrees.
